2>Tools</h2><h3>Monitoring</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/zjstraus/AES67-WebMeter\">AES67 WebMeter</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/zjstraus/AES67-WebMeter\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">6</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":6,\"repo\":\"zjstraus/AES67-WebMeter\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Server that receives an AES67 audio stream and presents a webpage with meters. <code>✓ open-source</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Monitoring</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/x42/meters.lv2\">meters.lv2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/x42/meters.lv2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">143</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":143,\"repo\":\"x42/meters.lv2\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - meters.lv2 is a collection of audio-level meters with GUI in LV2 plugin format. <code>✓ open-source</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Tools</h2><h3>Monitoring</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://opensoundmeter.com/\">Open Sound Meter</a> - Clean, open-source sound meter. Supports RTA, magnitude, phase and impulse response, coherence, group delay and more. <code>✓ open-source</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and frameworks</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.openlighting.org/ola/\">Open Lighting Architecture</a> - A framework for lighting control information. Supports a range of protocols and over a dozen of USB devices. <a href=\"https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola\">Source Code</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">503</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":503,\"repo\":\"OpenLightingProject/ola\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc/other</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BryanCrotaz/blender-artnet\">Blender ArtNet</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BryanCrotaz/blender-artnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">27</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":27,\"repo\":\"BryanCrotaz/blender-artnet\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Blender script to push ArtNet data to Evee lights. Runs at 30fps with Evee rendering in the viewport. <code>✓ open-source</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc/other</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cbdevnet/midimonster/\">MIDI Monster</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cbdevnet/midimonster/\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">344</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":344,\"repo\":\"cbdevnet/midimonster\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - MIDIMonster is a universal control and translation tool. It can translate between many different protocols such as MIDI, Artnet, sACN and OSC. <code>✓ open-source</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-22T11:41:06.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Libraries and frameworks</h2><h3>ArtNet Libraries</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hobbyquaker/artnet\">artnet</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/hobbyquaker/artnet\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">106</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":106,\"repo\":\"hobbyquaker/artnet\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Node.js module that can be used to send ArtDMX packages to an Art-Net node. <code>nodejs</code>.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-16T16:01:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reddit.com/r/lightingdesign/\">/r/lightingdesign</a> - The Reddit community for lighting designers worldwide.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-16T16:01:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://reddit.com/r/techtheatre/\">/r/techtheatre</a> - The reddit community for all production designers and technicians!</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-16T16:01:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>GrandMA2 tutorials</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lhYDUzWKz3M\">GMA2 colour picker tutorial</a> - A tutorial for how to add a colour picker in GrandMA2.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-05-16T16:01:23.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Visualizers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/grandma2/\">Ma3D</a> - <strong>Free</strong> lighting visualizer for GrandMA consoles/software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-18T00:42:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Audio tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.artalabs.hr/\">ARTA</a> - A collection of programs for audio measurements and analysis.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-18T00:42:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Misc/other</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.usedlighting.com/\">UsedLighting</a> - Marketplace for buying/selling used lighting hardware.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-17T10:29:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.mikewoodld.com/blog/\">mikewoodld.com/blog/</a> - Blog of Lighting Designer Mike Wood.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-17T08:22:37.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://notelek.com/blog/\">notelek.com/blog/</a> - LXR Stage Technology Blog.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-17T08:22:37.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Lighting Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.malighting.com/downloads/products/dot2/\">Dot2 software</a> - Free, offline software for the Dot2 consoles. Includes Dot2 onPC and Dot2 3D.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-17T08:20:55.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Graphics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://inkscape.org/\">Inkscape</a> - Inkscape is a professional vector graphics editor for Linux, Windows and macOS.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-17T08:00:33.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Audio Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.da-share.com/software/multiplay/\">da-Share MultiPlay</a> - MultiPlay is a Windows based program designed to play audio cues for theatre or corporate use. It is free to use.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-16T10:20:58.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://qlab.app/cookbook/\">QLab Cookbook</a> - The cookbook is a collection of projects, examples, and experiments using a broad range of QLab programming techniques including AppleScript, OSC, external control using QLab Remote, third-party MIDI and OSC controllers, and other software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-16T07:09:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/groups/chamsys.users/\">Chamsys Programmers and Users facebook group</a> - The best place to find information about Chamsys consoles and software.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T23:43:38.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://geezersofgear.libsyn.com/\">Geezers of Gear</a> - Entertainment Production Industry veteran talking about pro-audio, lighting, staging, video + the people and companies who work in this great industry.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T23:43:38.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Lighting Software</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://chamsyslighting.com/\">Chamsys MagicQ</a> - MagiQ is a professional lighting software providing up to 64 Artnet universes for free. It includes powerful features like 2D/3D pixel mapping, effect generator, media server and visualizer.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T23:30:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h3>Audio tools</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.roomeqwizard.com/\">REW</a> - REW is free room acoustics analysis software for measuring and analysing room and loudspeaker responses. Free SMAART alternative.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T22:46:05.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCdLor-EVzOjOY7OZNXt8eIw\">Christian Jackson</a> - YouTube channel about concert lighting. Also has great MA tutorials.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T16:47:30.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/limelightwired/\">@limelightwired</a> - Lighting production community on Instagram.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-04-15T15:48:47.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/notlmn/awesome-icons","repo":"notlmn/awesome-icons"},"next":{"id":"awesomes/github.com/mfkl/awesome-vlc","repo":"mfkl/awesome-vlc"}},"pageContext":{"repo":"stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual","id":"awesomes/github.com/stingalleman/awesome-audiovisual","previousId":"awesomes/github.com/notlmn/awesome-icons","nextId":"awesomes/github.com/mfkl/awesome-vlc"}},"staticQueryHashes":["228695001","2744905544","2828988102"]}